    <briefdescription>
<para>Hardware pin abstraction for <ref refid="namespaceOpenSkyhawk" kindref="compound">OpenSkyhawk</ref> panel controls. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Abstracts four hardware pin sources behind a single interface: direct STM32 GPIO, MCP23017 expander GPIO, <ref refid="classADS1115" kindref="compound">ADS1115</ref> ADC channel, and a ShiftBus bit (74HC165 input / 74HC595 output over SPI). Used by all input and output classes so control declarations are identical regardless of where the physical pin lives.</para>
<para>Contains no logic beyond read/write dispatch — no debounce, no filtering, no state. <ref refid="classPinRef" kindref="compound">PinRef</ref> objects are value types: live on the stack or as class members, never heap-allocated.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="version"><para>0.1.0 </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="copyright"><para>GPL-2.0-only — see Firmware/LICENSE </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
